The military police
were at the door

258
00:11:58,141 --> 00:11:59,761
looking for you.

259
00:12:00,282 --> 00:12:02,991
- What did you tell them?
- I told them you weren't here.

260
00:12:03,020 --> 00:12:05,204
Oh. Thanks.
See you at dinner.

261
00:12:13,376 --> 00:12:16,244
Are you kidding
me, Jake? AWOL?

262
00:12:16,282 --> 00:12:18,183
Come on, it's not
that big a deal.

263
00:12:18,206 --> 00:12:20,655
You could go to jail!

264
00:12:20,667 --> 00:12:23,982
Really?
That seems a little extreme.

265
00:12:24,448 --> 00:12:26,753
All right, all right, enough.
Just go get your things,

266
00:12:26,776 --> 00:12:28,142
and I'll drive you back
to the base.

267
00:12:28,153 --> 00:12:29,686
No. I'm staying
here with Missi.

268
00:12:29,693 --> 00:12:31,586
This is not a discussion.
Let's go!

269
00:12:31,592 --> 00:12:33,514
Dad, I'm not a kid anymore.

270
00:12:33,531 --> 00:12:35,943
I'm 18, and I'm in the army.

271
00:12:36,330 --> 00:12:39,291
You're using the excuse
that you're in the army

272
00:12:39,319 --> 00:12:41,472
to not go back to the army?

273
00:12:41,668 --> 00:12:44,112
Hey, why don't you let me
go try to talk to him?

274
00:12:44,144 --> 00:12:45,644
You think you can bring him
back to his senses?

275
00:12:45,646 --> 00:12:47,829
Oh, yeah, I'm real good at getting
people to do what I want 'em to do—

276
00:12:47,852 --> 00:12:49,682
back home they call me
the "People Whisperer"

277
00:12:49,691 --> 00:12:50,970
It's kind of like
the Horse Whisperer,

278
00:12:50,984 --> 00:12:52,975
except I do it with people
and I don't really whisper.

279
00:12:52,989 --> 00:12:54,390
Ooh, I tried it with
a horse one time.

280
00:12:54,404 --> 00:12:56,054
He was just looking
at me like I was crazy.

281
00:12:56,076 --> 00:12:57,442
Kind of like you're
doing right now.

282
00:12:57,468 --> 00:12:59,380
I'll go talk to Jake.

283
00:13:00,608 --> 00:13:03,053
She cannot become
my daughter-in-law.

284
00:13:07,200 --> 00:13:08,967
Oh, good, you're
going back.

285
00:13:09,001 --> 00:13:11,369
Nope. You and me
are getting out of here.

286
00:13:11,398 --> 00:13:12,700
Where are we going?

287
00:13:12,718 --> 00:13:14,554
Doesn't matter.
I just want to be with you.

288
00:13:14,574 --> 00:13:17,259
Jake, I got to go back home;
I have a job.

289
00:13:17,261 --> 00:13:20,011
Hey, if I can leave the army,
you can leave your job.

290
00:13:20,013 --> 00:13:21,523
Whoa, slow down.

291
00:13:21,537 --> 00:13:24,872
Why? I love you
and you love me, right?

292
00:13:26,219 --> 00:13:27,730
Right?

293
00:13:28,884 --> 00:13:30,013
Jake...

294
00:13:30,033 --> 00:13:33,093
you have to know
how much I really like you.

295
00:13:33,225 --> 00:13:35,436
Oh, man.

296
00:13:35,527 --> 00:13:36,743
But...

297
00:13:36,762 --> 00:13:38,273
you're in good company,

298
00:13:38,294 --> 00:13:40,680
'cause I only really like
great things.

299
00:13:40,703 --> 00:13:43,099
You know, like
ice cream sundaes

300
00:13:43,123 --> 00:13:44,749
and jumping up and
down on bubble wrap

301
00:13:44,764 --> 00:13:46,527
and that cute little bear
in the toilet paper commercial

302
00:13:46,544 --> 00:13:48,544
that wipes his butt
on the trees.

303
00:13:48,784 --> 00:13:51,916
Okay, I heard it that time.
I do got to shut up.

304
00:13:55,986 --> 00:13:58,347
I brought you another beer.

305
00:13:58,366 --> 00:13:59,899
I don't know if I should.

306
00:13:59,926 --> 00:14:02,040
Oh, come on, drunk guys are hot.

307
00:14:02,098 --> 00:14:04,018
You know,
I got to tell you, Whitney,

308
00:14:04,037 --> 00:14:06,638
I am having
the best time with you.

309
00:14:06,665 --> 00:14:09,918
Good. 'Cause...
I think you're wonderful.

310
00:14:10,756 --> 00:14:12,557
Thanks.

311
00:14:14,183 --> 00:14:16,268
Do you really mean that?

312
00:14:16,270 --> 00:14:17,485
Of course I do.

313
00:14:17,509 --> 00:14:19,498
You're smart,
you're funny,

314
00:14:19,519 --> 00:14:21,969
not to mention very handsome.

315
00:14:22,007 --> 00:14:23,807
Ah. Too late,
you mentioned it.

316
00:14:25,375 --> 00:14:27,168
You know, but seriously...

317
00:14:27,196 --> 00:14:29,362
I am so glad I met you.

318
00:14:29,941 --> 00:14:31,127
Thanks.

319
00:14:31,140 --> 00:14:32,973
Me, too.

320
00:14:35,835 --> 00:14:37,888
See, here's the thing.

321
00:14:39,212 --> 00:14:40,742
I really mean it.

322
00:14:40,761 --> 00:14:42,177
So do I.

323
00:14:42,179 --> 00:14:44,248
Okay, see, I don't know
if you're just saying that

324
00:14:44,270 --> 00:14:45,665
because I'm paying you,

325
00:14:45,685 --> 00:14:47,969
or if you really believe it.

326
00:14:47,991 --> 00:14:50,408
How does it feel to you?

327
00:14:51,249 --> 00:14:53,304
It feels like you mean it.

328
00:14:53,493 --> 00:14:55,505
Then that's all that matters.

329
00:14:55,578 --> 00:14:57,239
Wh... No, it's not.

330
00:14:57,259 --> 00:14:59,843
See... I want to know

331
00:14:59,855 --> 00:15:01,900
if it's for real real

332
00:15:01,921 --> 00:15:04,588
or if it's "Best Performance
by a Girlfriend

333
00:15:04,607 --> 00:15:06,941
Hired in a Library" real.

334
00:15:06,989 --> 00:15:09,400
Because on my end, it is real.

335
00:15:09,815 --> 00:15:11,698
Me, too.

336
00:15:12,001 --> 00:15:14,348
Okay, if I wasn't paying you,

337
00:15:14,458 --> 00:15:16,360
would you still feel that?

338
00:15:16,396 --> 00:15:19,275
It wouldn't matter
if you were paying me or not.

339
00:15:19,416 --> 00:15:20,884
But I am paying you.

340
00:15:20,904 --> 00:15:23,512
Which doesn't change
the way I feel.

341
00:15:25,055 --> 00:15:27,178
Okay, let's try this
another way.

342
00:15:28,424 --> 00:15:31,643
I want you to feel

343
00:15:31,645 --> 00:15:33,845
that it's really real...

344
00:15:33,847 --> 00:15:36,264
for real real.

345
00:15:36,480 --> 00:15:37,820
And that...

346
00:15:37,846 --> 00:15:40,263
is exactly how I feel.

347
00:15:40,672 --> 00:15:42,549
Son of a bitch!

348
00:15:48,873 --> 00:15:50,157
Hey.

349
00:15:50,343 --> 00:15:51,658
Hey.

350
00:15:51,694 --> 00:15:52,869
You okay?

351
00:15:52,893 --> 00:15:54,150
What do you care?

352
00:15:54,164 --> 00:15:56,231
Come on, Jake, you know I care.

353
00:15:57,092 --> 00:15:58,957
I feel so stupid.

354
00:15:58,977 --> 00:16:00,326
No.

355
00:16:01,059 --> 00:16:03,325
You're not stupid.

356
00:16:05,060 --> 00:16:06,511
You want to hear stupid?

357
00:16:06,536 --> 00:16:09,068
One time I drank an entire
blueberry Slurpee in one slurp,

358
00:16:09,082 --> 00:16:12,217
had a three-hour brain freeze
and my pee looked like Windex.

359
00:16:12,402 --> 00:16:14,285
What the hell
are you talking about?

360
00:16:14,315 --> 00:16:17,149
I don't know,
I'm not real good with silence.

361
00:16:17,319 --> 00:16:20,693
Just... promise me
you'll go back to the army.

362
00:16:21,306 --> 00:16:23,644
Yeah, I'm going back.

363
00:16:23,707 --> 00:16:25,323
Good.

364
00:16:26,265 --> 00:16:29,267
Hey... we did have
some fun, though, right?

365
00:16:29,617 --> 00:16:31,751
Yeah, we did.

366
00:16:32,004 --> 00:16:34,548
Well, just remember that part.

367
00:16:38,994 --> 00:16:40,962
Good-bye, Jake.

368
00:16:52,953 --> 00:16:56,039
Where am I gonna find
another girl named Missi?

369
00:17:00,095 --> 00:17:01,612
Hey.

370
00:17:01,898 --> 00:17:03,448
Hey.

371
00:17:04,117 --> 00:17:05,410
Where's your new girlfriend?

372
00:17:05,435 --> 00:17:07,580
Ah, she's off
for the day.

373
00:17:08,720 --> 00:17:10,498
Where's your boyfriend?

374
00:17:10,531 --> 00:17:13,282
We... kind of broke up.

375
00:17:13,305 --> 00:17:14,854
How come?

376
00:17:14,867 --> 00:17:17,782
You know, I just thought I was
coming here for a fun weekend,

377
00:17:17,814 --> 00:17:19,719
no strings attached, but...

378
00:17:19,749 --> 00:17:21,584
then Jake told me
that he loved me

379
00:17:21,606 --> 00:17:23,339
and I just couldn't say it back.

380
00:17:23,363 --> 00:17:24,331
Ouch.

381
00:17:24,360 --> 00:17:26,705
I wasn't trying to hurt him.
It's just...

382
00:17:27,844 --> 00:17:30,028
he's not my soul mate.

383
00:17:30,030 --> 00:17:32,663
Well, I hate to break it to you,

384
00:17:32,665 --> 00:17:35,467
but... there is no such thing.

385
00:17:35,469 --> 00:17:36,905
That's not true.

386
00:17:36,914 --> 00:17:38,742
Everybody has a soul mate.

387
00:17:38,772 --> 00:17:40,104
And when
you find yours,

388
00:17:40,106 --> 00:17:41,396
it's like that feeling you get

389
00:17:41,411 --> 00:17:43,157
after the first big
snowfall of the year.

390
00:17:43,172 --> 00:17:44,843
You race outside
to go sledding

391
00:17:44,861 --> 00:17:47,533
and you go to the top of
the steepest hill you can find,

392
00:17:47,567 --> 00:17:49,544
and, you know, your heart starts
racing and you get all sweaty,

393
00:17:49,566 --> 00:17:51,873
even though all your boogers
are frozen over,

394
00:17:51,903 --> 00:17:53,069
and... the next
thing you know,

395
00:17:53,086 --> 00:17:54,569
you are zipping down
Montague Street,

396
00:17:54,571 --> 00:17:57,287
laughing and crying
all at the same time,

397
00:17:57,310 --> 00:17:59,176
and you never want it to end.

398
00:17:59,201 --> 00:18:01,635
And that's what real love
should feel like.

399
00:18:02,561 --> 00:18:05,396
Nobody should settle
for anything less.

400
00:18:06,198 --> 00:18:08,310
Remember when I told you
to shut up earlier?

401
00:18:08,334 --> 00:18:09,626
I'm sorry. I know.

402
00:18:09,641 --> 00:18:11,117
No.

403
00:18:11,204 --> 00:18:13,972
Don't ever listen to me again.

404
00:18:14,890 --> 00:18:17,025
'Cause that was awesome.

405
00:18:20,350 --> 00:18:21,684
Where you going?

406
00:18:21,701 --> 00:18:23,429
I'm gonna go see
if my girlfriend

407
00:18:23,442 --> 00:18:26,036
wants to really
be my girlfriend.

408
00:18:27,823 --> 00:18:30,825
And the People Whisperer
strikes again.

409
00:18:33,914 --> 00:18:35,856
And we're flying
down the hill

410
00:18:35,871 --> 00:18:37,171
and you're all sweaty

411
00:18:37,197 --> 00:18:39,694
and there are, like,
boogers frozen everywhere,

412
00:18:39,749 --> 00:18:41,646
and... the point is,

413
00:18:41,673 --> 00:18:44,507
I want to share
that feeling with you.

414
00:18:45,579 --> 00:18:47,480
For real.

415
00:18:47,873 --> 00:18:49,819
I'm gay.

416
00:18:52,575 --> 00:18:53,854
What?

417
00:18:53,860 --> 00:18:55,953
I like women.

418
00:18:56,491 --> 00:18:58,441
For real?

419
00:18:58,663 --> 00:19:00,533
For real.

420
00:19:00,585 --> 00:19:02,237
Wow.

421
00:19:02,283 --> 00:19:04,766
You're a really good actor.

422
00:19:05,641 --> 00:19:06,941
Thank you.

423
00:19:07,134 --> 00:19:09,051
Do you want to go
to a movie tomorrow?

424
00:19:09,069 --> 00:19:11,175
Sure, yeah.
That sounds great.

425
00:19:12,132 --> 00:19:13,223
I love you.

426
00:19:13,234 --> 00:19:14,464
Love you, too, honey!

427
00:19:20,909 --> 00:19:22,444
You all right, buddy?

428
00:19:22,445 --> 00:19:24,476
I'm fine.

429
00:19:25,255 --> 00:19:27,222
It's okay to be upset.

430
00:19:27,259 --> 00:19:29,445
I'm not upset.

431
00:19:30,845 --> 00:19:33,644
if you were, I-I
would understand.

432
00:19:33,836 --> 00:19:36,436
I mean, you give
yourself to somebody,

433
00:19:36,463 --> 00:19:39,548
you finally let down
all your walls, and...

434
00:19:39,802 --> 00:19:42,052
then they break
your heart.

435
00:19:42,253 --> 00:19:43,921
Yeah.

436
00:19:44,577 --> 00:19:47,272
I'm really sorry
you have to go through this.

437
00:19:47,302 --> 00:19:48,646
I mean...

438
00:19:48,688 --> 00:19:51,803
