to see you in pain.

439
00:19:51,986 --> 00:19:55,024
I mean, I-I know
you're a soldier now,

440
00:19:55,160 --> 00:19:58,575
but... you're still
my little baby boy.

441
00:19:58,680 --> 00:20:01,253
You know, I-I remember bringing
you home from the hospital,

442
00:20:01,270 --> 00:20:04,188
wrapped in your...
fuzzy blue blanket.

443
00:20:05,692 --> 00:20:08,400
I love you so much.

444
00:20:08,974 --> 00:20:10,767
I just...
I-I just wish

445
00:20:10,778 --> 00:20:13,009
I hurt instead
of you.

446
00:20:13,237 --> 00:20:15,130
Dad... it's okay.

447
00:20:15,149 --> 00:20:17,314
No, no, it's not okay!

448
00:20:17,841 --> 00:20:19,347
Maybe I should drive.

449
00:20:19,358 --> 00:20:21,660
Yeah, yeah, that's
a good idea.

450
00:20:21,871 --> 00:20:23,522
Thank you.

451
00:20:24,279 --> 00:20:26,363
All I'm saying is,
you can't give up.

452
00:20:26,389 --> 00:20:28,034
Your soul mate's
out there.

453
00:20:28,058 --> 00:20:29,290
Yeah, I don't know, Missi.

454
00:20:29,299 --> 00:20:31,604
You just got to keep
your eyes and your heart open.

455
00:20:31,620 --> 00:20:33,128
You know, you never know
where you're gonna find her.

456
00:20:33,142 --> 00:20:34,532
